<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="768" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/898a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)<note n="93" xml:id="d768fn93">The same on the same date to the diplomatic
                                    representatives in Colombia (No. 60), Cuba (No. 137), and
                                    Uruguay (No. 24).</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-09T19:00:00-05:00">December 9, 1929—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>538. Department’s 536, December 6, 4 p.m. It is of course understood
                                that the communication in question will not be sent to the <pb facs="1067" n="931" xml:id="pg_931"/> Bolivian Government until
                                it has been agreed to by all the neutral Governments. When this is
                                done a date will be fixed by mutual agreement on which to transmit
                                it.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>